Therefore, cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing) and cs.SI (Signal Processing) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper also discusses the concept of higher order entropy and its application in clustering and classification, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper also mentions the potential use of these techniques in other disciplines for pattern recognition and machine learning, which could be relevant to the sub-category of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
